TY  - JOUR
AU  - Jin, Xing
AU  - Zhang, Allen X.
T1  - Decomposition of Optimal Portfolio Weight in a Jump-Diffusion Model and Its Applications
PY  - 2012
Y1  - 2012/09/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhs083
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 25
IS  - 9
SP  - 2877
EP  - 2919
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - This article solves the portfolio choice problem in a multi-asset jump-diffusion model. We decompose the optimal portfolio weight into components that correspond to a collection of fictitious economies, one of which is a standard diffusion economy, and the others of which are pure-jump economies. We derive a semi-closed-form solution for the optimal portfolio weight, and investigate its properties with or without ambiguity aversion. We find that an investor may not reduce her investment in risky assets when facing more frequent jumps, as suggested by a single-asset jump-diffusion model. Moreover, an investor who is extremely cautious about her estimates of higher moments of asset returns may still hold risky assets, contrary to the prediction of a pure-diffusion model with ambiguity aversion to the first moment.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhs083
ER  - 



